{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# ACLI subprocess 429 handling: honor Retry-After if available, else jittered backoff\n\n## Context / corrected premise\nThere is no separate \"bulk path\" — all ACLI calls go through the `_run_acli` subprocess (`acli_subprocess.py`),\nwhich sees only returncode + text stdout/stderr, NOT an HTTP `Retry-After` header object (unlike the REST helper\n`acli_rest.py`, which reads `exc.headers`). So \"parse Retry-After\" on the subprocess path is an UNVERIFIED\ncapability and must be proven before it is relied on.\n\n## What / files (`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_subprocess.py`)\n1. PROBE FIRST (spike): run `acli jira workitem search` against a rate-limited/staged endpoint; capture exit code\n   + stderr/stdout on 429 and determine whether ACLI surfaces `Retry-After` in any parseable form. Record the\n   finding on this ticket.\n2. If ACLI surfaces it: extract via regex from stderr (e.g. `Retry-After:\\s*(\\d+)`) and honor it. If it does\n   NOT: honor 429 with jittered exponential backoff WITHOUT Retry-After, and document that Retry-After is\n   unavailable on the subprocess path (behavior parity, not mechanism parity, with the REST helper).\n3. Retryable-code change is EXPLICIT: today `_run_acli` retries all non-zero `CalledProcessError` except\n   401/assignee. Decide + document: ADD selective 429/502/503 backoff ON TOP (recommended) vs NARROW to only\n   {429,502,503} (a behavior change) — do not silently narrow.\n4. PRESERVE the non-idempotent-write guard: `AcliTimeoutError` is deliberately not a `TimeoutError`, so a\n   timed-out write is not blindly retried — keep this.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Probe result recorded: whether ACLI surfaces Retry-After on 429 (with the observed text shape).\n- [ ] 429 on the subprocess path backs off with jittered exponential backoff; honors Retry-After IFF the probe confirmed availability (else documented unavailable).\n- [ ] Retryable-code change explicit + documented (add-on vs narrow); no silent narrowing.\n- [ ] Non-idempotent writes retain the no-blind-retry-on-timeout guard; test `test_acli_create_timeout_not_retried`.\n- [ ] Unit test: a simulated 429 triggers backoff (and Retry-After honoring, if available).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783475102815305001,"uuid":"1fa0e0c7-ffe8-4f7b-84ca-094bd1d71f41"}